Trade: Imports exceed exports. The structure of foreign trade has been unchanged for many years. Foreign trade has shifted in the past few years from CIS markets to markets of WTO member countries. Precious metals and products made from them are the main exports while mineral fuels are the main imports. Gold, 33-50% of total exports. Other exports include: metals (mercury, antimony), agricultural & food products, tobacco, cotton, and fruits & vegetables. Imports: oil, gas, iron, chemicals, pharmaceuticals, and machine tools.
